You are debugging a production issue where a high-throughput Spring Boot microservice is experiencing gradual heap exhaustion and eventual `OutOfMemoryError: Java heap space`. The service processes batch requests using a `FixedThreadPool` and sets custom metadata in a `ThreadLocal` variable for logging. You find this code snippet in a `Service` class:

java
@Service
public class RequestProcessor {
    private static final ThreadLocal<UserContext> contextHolder = new ThreadLocal<>();

    public void process(Request request) {
        contextHolder.set(new UserContext(request.getHeaders()));
        try {
            validate(request);
            enrich(request);
            save(request);
        } finally {
            // Context cleanup intended here
            if (request.isAsync()) {
                return; 
            }
            contextHolder.remove();
        }
    }
}

